#week-title("Four", "The Three Fires & The Hermetical Triumph")

=== Core Teaching

*The Hermetical Triumph* is one of the great classical texts on the antimony
work and provides the primary procedural framework for Year Three Month 1.
It opens with a philosophical distinction that shapes everything that follows:
the three fires of the alchemical work.

*The Three Fires:*

1. *The Elementary Fire* — common combustion; the fire under the flask; the
   charcoal or electrical heat that the practitioner applies externally. This
   is the most accessible fire and the one most easily misunderstood as the
   only fire. The sophist works with the Elementary Fire alone and produces
   chemistry, not alchemy.

2. *The Metallic Fire (Philosophic Mercury)* — the fire that is found within
   the metals themselves; the universal vital force in its mineral expression.
   This is the fire that the Elementary Fire is meant to awaken and support.
   When the Elementary Fire is applied correctly to the right matter in the
   right vessel, it excites the Metallic Fire into activity — and from that
   point the preparation begins to proceed through its own inner dynamics. This
   is why the tradition speaks of sealed vessels and long digestions: the
   Elementary Fire is only needed to initiate the Metallic Fire; thereafter,
   the Metallic Fire sustains the Work.

3. *The Magical Fire* — the Secret Fire of the matter itself; the concentrated
   expression of the World Spirit within the mineral. This is not applied from
   outside at all — it is drawn forth from within by the action of the first two
   fires in the correct proportion. The practitioner who has developed sensitivity
   to the inner fire through two years of meditation practice will, at some point
   in the mineral work, recognise this third fire operating. It cannot be
   produced by technique alone; it arises when the conditions are correct.

*The Butyrum of Antimony.* The Hermetical Triumph centres its first practical
sequence on the preparation of the Butyrum Antimonii — the "Butter of Antimony."
This is produced by working the Regulus of Antimony (the purified metallic
antimony separated from its sulphur by fusion) with a corrosive solvent, yielding
an unctuous, butter-like substance said to contain the Sulphur and Mercury of the
Wise in a combined, accessible form. This preparation belongs to the advanced
portion of Year Three Month 1 and requires full PPE and confirmed ventilation.

For this week, the student studies the Three Fires philosophically and reviews
the Butyrum preparation in the text without undertaking it practically — that
awaits the Year Three Safety Quiz confirmation and full PPE acquisition.

=== Topics This Week

- The Three Fires: Elementary, Metallic, and Magical
- The relationship between the three fires: initiation, sustaining, arising
- The Butyrum of Antimony: what it is and its role in the Hermetical Triumph sequence
- Comparing the vegetable kingdom's secret fire (from Year One) with the mineral
  kingdom's secret fire
- Review of Month 1 and preparation for Quarter I Gathering

#inner-work[
  *DES-2: Stop Images Confronted*

  Continue the DES-2 analytical depth work. This week: descend in the waking
  dream and identify specifically any stop images that have appeared. Do not
  flee them — address them directly with the analytical attention that DES-2
  describes.

  A stop image at this stage of the practitioner's development will typically
  have different qualities than those encountered in Year One Month 6. Record
  the encounter honestly: what did the figure or obstruction represent? What
  happened when you remained present with it rather than withdrawing?
]

